{
  "analysis": "The encoder still fails for non-empty streams: /app/decomp outputs nothing, and decsim decodes wrong token counts/tokens. The most likely remaining bug is normalization: the decoder normalizes at the start of get_bit before evaluating the bit, so the encoder must normalize before computing the bit interval, not after updating range. Also, the encoder currently does not maintain fraction. We need an exact decoder-state-driven encoder that keeps low/range/fraction and emits bytes when the decoder would read. Before building that, a small probe can empirically reveal how raw bytes decode into token-count bits and validate our understanding.",
  "plan": "Create a probe program that simulates the decoder for a single-byte stream by initializing range=255 and fraction=byte-1, then decodes the token-count integer and reports decoded token counts for all 255 byte values. This will show what raw first bytes mean to the decoder and help verify the arithmetic coding model before rewriting the encoder.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "cat > /app/probe1.c <<'C'
#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>
#define W for (i=0;i<tmp;i++)
int i;
int radix = 255;
int fraction;
long range = 1;
int tmp;
int cc[1000000];
int OFF1 = 5, OFF2 = 2, LITSIZE = 4;
int get_bit(int ctx) {
  int *counts = cc + ctx * 2;
  int split = range * -~*counts / (*counts + counts[ 1 ] + 2);
  int the_bit = fraction >= split;
  fraction -= split*the_bit;
  range = the_bit ? range-split : split;
  counts[ the_bit ]++;
  return the_bit;
}
int get_integer_probe(int tmp0, int ctx) {
  int subtract_it = 1<<tmp0;
  int result_ans = 1;
  ctx*=99;
  int b;
  while ((b=get_bit(++tmp0+ctx))==0) {
    fprintf(stderr,"  bit0 ctx=%d split? bit=0 range=%ld fraction=%d\n",tmp0+ctx,range,fraction);
  }
  fprintf(stderr,"  bit1 ctx=%d bit=1 range=%ld fraction=%d\n",tmp0+ctx,range,fraction);
  tmp0--;
  W {
    b=get_bit(ctx);
    result_ans = result_ans*2 | b;
    fprintf(stderr,"  bitb ctx=%d bit=%d range=%ld fraction=%d\n",ctx,b,range,fraction);
  }
  return result_ans - subtract_it;
}
int main(int argc,char**argv){
  int start=1,end=255;
  if(argc>=2) start=atoi(argv[1]);
  if(argc>=3) end=atoi(argv[2]);
  for (int byte=start;byte<=end;byte++) {
    memset(cc,0,sizeof(cc));
    range=255; fraction=byte-1;
    int tok=get_integer_probe(9,0);
    if (tok>=0 && tok<=20) printf("byte=%d tok=%d range=%ld fraction=%d\n",byte,tok,range,fraction);
  }
  return 0;
}
